Description:
In this poignant performance, the legendary Mstislav Rostropovich joins the NHK Symphony Orchestra under the baton of Seiji Ozawa to deliver an emotional rendition of Dvořák's Cello Concerto. As a marked tribute to the thousands affected by tragedy, Rostropovich's heartfelt sentiments set the stage for a reflective moment, culminating in a moving interpretation of Bach's Sarabande. Witness the power of music as it transforms sorrow into a shared prayer for the departed, binding hearts together in silence and remembrance. A truly unforgettable experience that showcases both artistry and compassion.
